Let's look at such a metric as marketing costs.

38:54.000 --> 38:57.000
Any company should understand what its marketing costs are

38:58.000 --> 38:59.000
and be sure to take them into account.

39:00.000 --> 39:03.000
But the knowledge of marketing costs in units of money

39:04.000 --> 39:06.000
does not always give the right answer.

39:06.000 --> 39:09.000
You can't compare the marketing costs of other companies,

39:10.000 --> 39:12.000
because they may depend on the scale of the activity.

39:13.000 --> 39:16.000
And for this, companies often calculate the marketing costs

39:17.000 --> 39:19.000
as a percentage of the sales volume.

39:20.000 --> 39:23.000
In many industries, there are some common standards

39:24.000 --> 39:27.000
about the average marketing costs of companies in this industry.

39:28.000 --> 39:30.000
And knowing this standard,

39:31.000 --> 39:33.000
you can calculate the marketing costs

39:33.000 --> 39:35.000
of companies in this industry.

39:36.000 --> 39:38.000
Knowing this average level,

39:39.000 --> 39:42.000
a company can compare its own indicator with the average

39:43.000 --> 39:45.000
and understand whether it spends more or less.

39:46.000 --> 39:48.000
And if it spends more, is it justified?

39:49.000 --> 39:50.000
And why does it do it?

39:51.000 --> 39:54.000
That is, to make a conscious decision to spend more on marketing than competitors.

