52:44.000 --> 52:45.000
To calculate the coefficient of trial purchases,

52:46.000 --> 52:47.000
we need to divide the number of buyers

52:48.000 --> 52:49.000
who tried the product

52:50.000 --> 52:51.000
by the total number of potential buyers.

52:53.000 --> 52:54.000
The coefficient of repeated purchases

52:55.000 --> 52:56.000
is the ratio of the number of buyers

52:57.000 --> 52:58.000
who bought our product again

52:59.000 --> 53:00.000
to all those who tried it.

