57:46.000 --> 57:47.000
Now, let's move on to the next metric

57:48.000 --> 57:49.000
within the framework of the company's

57:50.000 --> 57:51.000
product policy.

57:52.000 --> 57:53.000
This metric is associated with the concept

57:54.000 --> 57:55.000
of commodity cannibalism.

57:56.000 --> 57:57.000
This situation occurs when

57:58.000 --> 57:59.000
a new product appears in the company.

58:00.000 --> 58:01.000
And inevitably, this new product

58:02.000 --> 58:03.000
eats up part of the volume of sales

58:04.000 --> 58:05.000
of the old product.

58:06.000 --> 58:07.000
To determine which part of the volume of sales

58:08.000 --> 58:09.000
of the old product will be eaten up

58:10.000 --> 58:11.000
by a new product,

58:12.000 --> 58:13.000
we use the coefficient of cannibalization.

58:14.000 --> 58:15.000
We divide the lost sales,

58:16.000 --> 58:17.000
that is, the sales that we lost

58:18.000 --> 58:19.000
as a result of the introduction

58:20.000 --> 58:21.000
of a new product into the market

58:21.000 --> 58:22.000
as a result of the introduction

58:23.000 --> 58:24.000
of a new product into the market,

58:25.000 --> 58:26.000
that is, the sale of an old product,

58:27.000 --> 58:28.000
into the volume of sales of a new product.

58:29.000 --> 58:30.000
And what does this coefficient of cannibalization

58:31.000 --> 58:32.000
allow us to understand?

58:33.000 --> 58:34.000
It shows us whether it is reasonable

58:35.000 --> 58:36.000
from the point of view of the volume of sales

58:37.000 --> 58:38.000
and profits

58:39.000 --> 58:40.000
of introducing a new product into the market.

58:41.000 --> 58:42.000
If the coefficient of cannibalization

58:43.000 --> 58:44.000
is less than 100%,

58:45.000 --> 58:46.000
it turns out that we have lost

58:47.000 --> 58:48.000
the volume of sales less than we received

58:49.000 --> 58:50.000
due to the introduction of a new product

58:51.000 --> 58:52.000
into the market.

58:53.000 --> 58:54.000
There are situations when

58:55.000 --> 58:56.000
the coefficient of cannibalization

58:57.000 --> 58:58.000
is 100%.

58:59.000 --> 59:00.000
This means that a new product

59:01.000 --> 59:02.000
has completely replaced an old product.

59:03.000 --> 59:04.000
And here the change in the profit of the company

59:05.000 --> 59:06.000
depends on the margin

59:07.000 --> 59:08.000
of a new and old product.

59:09.000 --> 59:10.000
If the margin of a new product is greater,

59:11.000 --> 59:12.000
then the profit of the company will increase.

59:13.000 --> 59:14.000
There are situations when

59:15.000 --> 59:16.000
the coefficient of cannibalization

59:17.000 --> 59:18.000
exceeds 100%.

59:19.000 --> 59:20.000
What does this mean?

59:21.000 --> 59:22.000
The amount of new products

59:23.000 --> 59:24.000
has decreased to a greater extent

59:25.000 --> 59:26.000
than the volume of sales of new products.

59:27.000 --> 59:28.000
What can this be connected with?

59:29.000 --> 59:30.000
Usually, this happens in cases

59:31.000 --> 59:32.000
when buyers,

59:33.000 --> 59:34.000
having seen that a new product

59:35.000 --> 59:36.000
has appeared,

59:37.000 --> 59:38.000
improved, modified,

59:39.000 --> 59:40.000
more attractive,

59:41.000 --> 59:42.000
refuse to purchase an old product,

59:43.000 --> 59:44.000
but at the same time

59:45.000 --> 59:46.000
they have not yet purchased a new one,

59:47.000 --> 59:48.000
either because they do not have enough money

59:49.000 --> 59:50.000
to purchase it,

59:51.000 --> 59:52.000
but because they have not yet

59:53.000 --> 59:54.000
purchased a new product.

59:55.000 --> 59:56.000
In this case, the coefficient of cannibalization

59:57.000 --> 59:58.000
exceeds 100%.

59:59.000 --> 01:00:00.000
This can be dangerous for the company.

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:02.000
It turns out that it has lost

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:04.000
an old product,

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:06.000
and the new product has not yet

01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:08.000
started to work in the market.

