01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:12.000
Now we move on to the metrics related to advertising.

01:14:13.000 --> 01:14:16.000
The main metrics used in advertising and media planning

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:21.000
are impression, coverage, frequency and assessment coefficients.

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:23.000
What does it all mean?

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.000
Impression is the number of potential contacts

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:29.000
of the target audience with our advertising message.

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:33.000
Coverage is the number of people,

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:35.000
the number of representatives of the target audience

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:40.000
who had the opportunity to see our advertising message

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:42.000
during a certain show.

01:14:43.000 --> 01:14:47.000
Pure coverage is the number of representatives of the target audience

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:51.000
who actually saw our advertising message.

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:54.000
The coverage is the number of people who could see it,

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:56.000
but we don't know if they saw it or not.

01:14:57.000 --> 01:14:58.000
Pure coverage is the number of people who saw it,

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:00.000
we know it.

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:04.000
This information is obtained during marketing research.

01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:07.000
Frequency is the number of times

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:10.000
the representative of the target audience

01:15:11.000 --> 01:15:14.000
could see our message on average.

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:18.000
And the more complex metric is the assessment coefficient

01:15:19.000 --> 01:15:20.000
or rating point.

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:23.000
The percentage of representatives of the target audience

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:26.000
who had the opportunity to see our advertising message

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:30.000
may seem to be the same as coverage.

01:15:31.000 --> 01:15:32.000
The target audience is the same,

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:37.000
and we count who could see our advertising message.

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:39.000
But in case of coverage,

01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:42.000
the number of people is the indicator.

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:44.000
In case of rating point,

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:46.000
the indicator is in percentages.

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:50.000
Although it is often indicated without the percentage sign.

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:54.000
If the rating point is 5,

01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:58.000
it means that 5% of the target audience

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:01.000
had the opportunity to see our advertising message.

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:04.000
If the coverage is 5,

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:06.000
it means that 5 people

01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:10.000
had the opportunity to see our advertising message.

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:14.000
And finally, the Graphical Rating Point.

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:16.000
Sometimes it is simply called GRP.

01:16:17.000 --> 01:16:18.000
It is the rating point

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:22.000
accumulated by all the indicators of our advertising message.

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:24.000
To better understand how it is calculated

01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:26.000
and what all these indicators mean,

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:28.000
let's look at an example.

01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:33.000
So, let's imagine that our target audience is 5 people.

01:16:34.000 --> 01:16:37.000
And we had 5 indicators of our advertising message.

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:39.000
You can see in the table

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:41.000
that the pluses mean that

01:16:42.000 --> 01:16:43.000
this representative of the target audience

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:45.000
had the opportunity to see our message.

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:47.000
The minuses mean that

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:50.000
he did not have the opportunity to see our advertising message

01:16:51.000 --> 01:16:52.000
at the time of this show.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:54.000
We are calculating the impression.

01:16:55.000 --> 01:16:58.000
Try to calculate the impression indicator yourself.

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:03.000
That is, the number of potential contacts of the target audience.

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:04.000
Calculating the impression

01:17:05.000 --> 01:17:07.000
and knowing what our target audience is in general,

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:09.000
that is, 100%,

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:11.000
and 100% is 5 people,

01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:14.000
we can calculate the rating point

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:17.000
as a percentage of those representatives of the target audience

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:19.000
who could see the message

01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:22.000
in relation to the audience of the target audience.

01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:24.000
And this percentage

01:17:25.000 --> 01:17:26.000
is calculated

01:17:27.000 --> 01:17:29.000
by the number of contacts of the target audience.

01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:30.000
And this percentage

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:32.000
is calculated

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:35.000
by the number of contacts of the target audience.

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:38.000
And when we calculate all the rating points,

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:40.000
that is, the points for each show,

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:42.000
we can add them up,

01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:44.000
and we get the value of the rating point.

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:46.000
Let's see what the answers should be.

