And so on.

01:18:08.000 --> 01:18:09.000
We calculate and, in the end,

01:18:10.000 --> 01:18:11.000
adding up all the rating points for each show,

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:13.000
we get the value of the rating point.

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:16.000
The next indicators used in media planning

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:18.000
are the effective frequency

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:20.000
and effective coverage.

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:23.000
You remember that frequency is the average number of times

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:25.000
that a representative of the target audience

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:27.000
could see our message.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:30.000
Effective frequency is the number of times

01:18:31.000 --> 01:18:32.000
that, in our opinion,

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:36.000
a customer needs to not only see,

01:18:37.000 --> 01:18:39.000
but also perceive, understand our message.

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:41.000
In many cases, it is quite obvious

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:45.000
that seeing the message once is not enough.

01:18:46.000 --> 01:18:49.000
The customer may not record anything from this message,

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:51.000
and, accordingly, it will not affect

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:54.000
his behavior when making purchases.

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:56.000
That is why, most often,

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:59.000
companies set a certain effective frequency,

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:01.000
that is, the minimum number of times

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:03.000
that the message should be seen

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:06.000
so that something happens in the customer's head,

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:08.000
so that it somehow affects his behavior.

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:10.000
And, having established an effective frequency,

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:13.000
we can calculate effective coverage.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:17.000
Effective coverage is the number of representatives

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:19.000
of the target audience

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:22.000
who could see our message

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:24.000
and the number of times that the message should be seen.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:26.000
That is, with an effective frequency.

01:19:27.000 --> 01:19:28.000
Look at the table.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:32.000
You see that here we have the number of representatives

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:34.000
of the target audience

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:37.000
who had the opportunity to see our message

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:39.000
with a certain number of times,

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:41.000
that is, with a certain frequency.

01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:43.000
