according to which they will further control

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:34.000
their marketing activity.

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:37.000
And, of course, according to each indicator,

01:22:38.000 --> 01:22:39.000
the company sets a certain goal,

01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:42.000
which it would like to achieve.

01:22:43.000 --> 01:22:44.000
At the stage of control,

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:46.000
we compare the target indicator

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:48.000
and the real one,

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:50.000
the one we have achieved

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:52.000
during a certain period.

01:22:53.000 --> 01:22:54.000
The indicators

01:22:55.000 --> 01:22:56.000
for which the control is carried out

01:22:57.000 --> 01:22:58.000
for the implementation of the plans

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:00.000
are divided into several groups.

01:23:01.000 --> 01:23:02.000
First, this is an analysis of the profitability.

01:23:03.000 --> 01:23:04.000
These are all indicators

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:06.000
related to the goals for profitability.

01:23:07.000 --> 01:23:10.000
Next, the goals for the market share are assessed.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:12.000
Have we achieved the market share

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:15.000
that was initially set as a goal?

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:18.000
Here we assess both the market share

01:23:19.000 --> 01:23:20.000
and the relative market share.

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:23.000
We also assess the level of our marketing costs.

01:23:24.000 --> 01:23:26.000
Have they exceeded the limit

01:23:27.000 --> 01:23:28.000
that we have set?

01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:30.000
And what is the ratio

01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:32.000
of the result obtained

01:23:33.000 --> 01:23:34.000
in terms of sales

01:23:34.000 --> 01:23:36.000
and the cost of the sales?

01:23:37.000 --> 01:23:38.000
Another integral part

01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:41.000
of the control for the implementation of the annual plans

01:23:42.000 --> 01:23:44.000
is monitoring the consumers.

01:23:45.000 --> 01:23:46.000
Here all the metrics are considered,

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:48.000
which are related to the consumers

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:50.000
we have talked about.

01:23:51.000 --> 01:23:52.000
We set goals for awareness,

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:56.000
for the perception of our product or our brand,

01:23:57.000 --> 01:23:58.000
for the attitude of the buyer,

01:23:59.000 --> 01:24:00.000
for the retention of the buyer,

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:02.000
and so on.

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:03.000
We also monitor

01:24:04.000 --> 01:24:05.000
whether we have achieved

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:07.000
the goals that we had set

01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:10.000
at the beginning of our planning.

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:12.000
We also monitor

01:24:13.000 --> 01:24:14.000
whether we have achieved something.

01:24:15.000 --> 01:24:18.000
We also conduct an analysis of the financial indicators

01:24:19.000 --> 01:24:22.000
related to the achievement of the desired level of profit,

01:24:23.000 --> 01:24:24.000
level of return,

01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:26.000
level of margin.

01:24:27.000 --> 01:24:28.000
After the company has determined

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:30.000
whether the real business situation

01:24:30.000 --> 01:24:31.000
is in line with the goals,

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:34.000
whether the goals we had set at the beginning

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:36.000
have been achieved,

01:24:37.000 --> 01:24:39.000
the next step is the control of profitability.

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:41.000
Here, as a rule,

01:24:42.000 --> 01:24:43.000
the main indicators of profitability are calculated,

01:24:44.000 --> 01:24:45.000
profitability of sales,

01:24:46.000 --> 01:24:47.000
profitability of investments

01:24:48.000 --> 01:24:49.000
and profitability of marketing investments.

01:24:50.000 --> 01:24:51.000
And finally, if the company sees

01:24:52.000 --> 01:24:53.000
that there are some problems

01:24:54.000 --> 01:24:55.000
with achieving the goals,

01:24:56.000 --> 01:24:57.000
that is,

01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:58.000
the sales goals are not achieved,

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:01.000
the market share does not correspond to the desired one,

01:25:02.000 --> 01:25:03.000
or the attitude to the product of the consumer

01:25:04.000 --> 01:25:06.000
is not what we would like to get,

01:25:07.000 --> 01:25:08.000
then we plan to carry out

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:10.000
such a rather large-scale event

01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:12.000
as a marketing audit.

01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:14.000
This is an independent study

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:16.000
of all the indicators of the company's activities,

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:18.000
which allows us to understand

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:20.000
what are the reasons

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:22.000
for the insufficient achievement of the goals

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:25.000
and what the company needs to change.

01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:26.000
The marketing audit

