01:27:07.000 --> 01:27:08.000
Now let's move on

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:10.000
to strategic control.

01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:12.000
To conduct control at a strategic level

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:14.000
means to understand

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:16.000
whether the company is moving

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:18.000
in the right direction in general

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:20.000
or there are some conceptual problems

01:27:21.000 --> 01:27:22.000
that do not allow it

01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:24.000
to be successful.

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:26.000
Strategic control consists of several stages.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:28.000
To begin with,

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:30.000
we traditionally set the parameters

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:32.000
of our strategy assessment.

01:27:33.000 --> 01:27:34.000
I mean the parameters of the strategy assessment,

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:37.000
not the processes we talked about earlier.

01:27:38.000 --> 01:27:39.000
After that, the company must ensure

01:27:40.000 --> 01:27:41.000
that all the necessary information

01:27:42.000 --> 01:27:43.000
for assessment

01:27:44.000 --> 01:27:45.000
is collected on a regular basis

01:27:46.000 --> 01:27:47.000
in order to have the opportunity

01:27:48.000 --> 01:27:49.000
to evaluate this information

01:27:50.000 --> 01:27:51.000
and use it for control.

01:27:52.000 --> 01:27:53.000
After we have collected information

01:27:54.000 --> 01:27:55.000
about our activity

01:27:56.000 --> 01:27:57.000
based on the selected parameters,

01:27:58.000 --> 01:27:59.000
we can compare

01:28:00.000 --> 01:28:01.000
the real and the desired parameters.

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:03.000
And according to the results,

01:28:04.000 --> 01:28:05.000
the company makes a decision

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:07.000
about the adjustment.

01:28:08.000 --> 01:28:09.000
What situations do we have?

01:28:10.000 --> 01:28:11.000
There is a situation

01:28:12.000 --> 01:28:13.000
when the planned results

01:28:14.000 --> 01:28:15.000
correspond to the real results.

01:28:16.000 --> 01:28:17.000
This is probably the simplest situation.

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:19.000
But it is not always like that.

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:20.000
There is a situation

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:22.000
when the real performance

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:24.000
of the company

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:26.000
is higher than the desired performance.

01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:28.000
It is higher than the desired performance.

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:30.000
What does it mean?

01:28:31.000 --> 01:28:32.000
We have overcompleted our plan?

01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:34.000
This is not good.

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:36.000
Why?

01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:38.000
It means that we have set

01:28:39.000 --> 01:28:40.000
inadequate goals.

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:42.000
We need to reconsider our goals.

01:28:43.000 --> 01:28:44.000
Maybe we have deliberately

01:28:45.000 --> 01:28:46.000
or unconsciously lowered the bar

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:48.000
and did not reach the results

01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:50.000
we could have achieved.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:52.000
In a situation when

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:54.000
the real performance is worse

01:28:55.000 --> 01:28:56.000
than the planned performance,

01:28:57.000 --> 01:28:58.000
the company usually

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:00.000
needs to make adjustments.

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:02.000
What does it mean to make adjustments?

01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:04.000
There are no obvious solutions.

01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:06.000
First of all,

01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:08.000
after we get

01:29:09.000 --> 01:29:10.000
a negative result,

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:12.000
we see that the implementation of the strategy

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:14.000
did not give us the desired results,

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:16.000
we should pay attention

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:18.000
to the selected parameters

01:29:19.000 --> 01:29:20.000
and evaluation indicators.

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:22.000
Maybe we have chosen

01:29:23.000 --> 01:29:24.000
the wrong evaluation indicators

01:29:25.000 --> 01:29:26.000
and that is why we have

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:28.000
not achieved a good result.

01:29:29.000 --> 01:29:30.000
If we have checked our parameters

01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:32.000
and decided that they were

01:29:33.000 --> 01:29:34.000
adequately selected

01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:36.000
in terms of the current market situation,

01:29:37.000 --> 01:29:38.000
we should think

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:40.000
if our goals are adequate.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:42.000
If we confirm that

01:29:43.000 --> 01:29:44.000
our goals are relevant

01:29:45.000 --> 01:29:46.000
and there is no point in changing them,

01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:48.000
we should pay attention

01:29:49.000 --> 01:29:50.000
to the strategy.

01:29:51.000 --> 01:29:52.000
Maybe the problem

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:54.000
in the implementation of the strategy

01:29:55.000 --> 01:29:56.000
is that the strategy was chosen

01:29:57.000 --> 01:29:58.000
incorrectly.

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:00.000
Only if we get a confirmation

01:30:01.000 --> 01:30:02.000
that the strategy was chosen

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:04.000
correctly and corresponds

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:06.000
to the current situation

01:30:07.000 --> 01:30:08.000
in the external and internal

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:10.000
environment of the company,

01:30:11.000 --> 01:30:12.000
only after that we make

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:14.000
a decision to adjust

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:16.000
the implementation of processes

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:18.000
and operations in the company.

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:20.000
We should make adjustments

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:22.000
to the evaluation indicators

01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:24.000
and the strategy before

01:30:25.000 --> 01:30:26.000
the adjustment of operations.

