01:30:43.000 --> 01:30:44.000
In conclusion,

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:46.000
I would like to note the following.

01:30:47.000 --> 01:30:48.000
First of all,

01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:50.000
the control of marketing activities

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:52.000
is certainly not a panacea.

01:30:53.000 --> 01:30:54.000
There are many situations

01:30:55.000 --> 01:30:56.000
when the control

01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:58.000
can only harm the company,

01:30:59.000 --> 01:31:01.000
namely, when the control is not carried out correctly.

01:31:02.000 --> 01:31:03.000
Let's look at several situations

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:05.000
when the control

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:08.000
can be carried out with some mistakes.

01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:10.000
First,

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:12.000
there is a common situation

01:31:13.000 --> 01:31:14.000
when the control becomes

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:16.000
not a means of achieving

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:18.000
a certain result,

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:20.000
when the company

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:22.000
carries out the control

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:24.000
only for the sake of

01:31:25.000 --> 01:31:26.000
the process of the control.

01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:28.000
And often in this situation

01:31:29.000 --> 01:31:30.000
the ordinary employees suffer,

01:31:31.000 --> 01:31:33.000
who are under constant control.

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:35.000
They do not see why

01:31:36.000 --> 01:31:37.000
this control is carried out

01:31:38.000 --> 01:31:39.000
and it really does not give anything to the company.

01:31:40.000 --> 01:31:41.000
The second situation is related to the fact

01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:43.000
that managers, as a result of large-scale

01:31:44.000 --> 01:31:45.000
control measures and evaluation of activities,

01:31:46.000 --> 01:31:47.000
are simply overwhelmed

01:31:47.000 --> 01:31:48.000
with information about the results,

01:31:49.000 --> 01:31:50.000
about the controlled indicators,

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:52.000
and they simply do not have time

01:31:53.000 --> 01:31:54.000
to figure out all the indicators

01:31:55.000 --> 01:31:56.000
they receive

01:31:57.000 --> 01:31:58.000
and in fact do not use them.

01:31:59.000 --> 01:32:00.000
That is, reports

01:32:01.000 --> 01:32:02.000
on the assessment of efficiency

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:04.000
simply fall on the shelf

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:06.000
and this does not give anything to the company.

01:32:07.000 --> 01:32:08.000
Such situations must also be avoided.

01:32:09.000 --> 01:32:10.000
And the third situation

01:32:11.000 --> 01:32:12.000
when the control can only harm the company

01:32:13.000 --> 01:32:14.000
occurs when the control

01:32:15.000 --> 01:32:16.000
is used

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:18.000
for other purposes.

01:32:19.000 --> 01:32:20.000
For example,

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:22.000
in some companies

01:32:23.000 --> 01:32:24.000
the control of the results of marketing activities

01:32:25.000 --> 01:32:26.000
is carried out

01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:28.000
exclusively to harm

01:32:29.000 --> 01:32:30.000
its employees in one way or another

01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:32.000
according to the results of this control.

01:32:33.000 --> 01:32:34.000
And often in such situations

01:32:35.000 --> 01:32:36.000
the results are bad.

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:38.000
More precisely, they are almost always bad

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:40.000
because the company sets

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:42.000
inevitably unattainable goals,

01:32:43.000 --> 01:32:44.000
inevitably overestimated.

01:32:45.000 --> 01:32:46.000
It turns out that this control

01:32:47.000 --> 01:32:48.000
is used by the company's top managers

01:32:49.000 --> 01:32:50.000
to achieve other goals

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:52.000
that have nothing to do

01:32:53.000 --> 01:32:54.000
with the efficiency of marketing.

